# README Generation

When asked to create a README:

1. Read @templates/README.template.md as the canonical structure.
2. Inspect the repository to populate placeholders factually — do not invent versions, owners, or URLs. If a value is unknown, ask before writing.
3. Preserve numbered section headings and page-break markers verbatim.
4. Sections 1, 2, 3, 4, and 12 are mandatory. Other sections may be deleted if genuinely inapplicable; renumber the remainder consecutively.
5. Remove the HTML instruction comment block at the top before saving.
6. Output to ./README.md at the repo root unless instructed otherwise.